":["form of   Isabel  , now in frequent use in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]},{"name":"Isobelle","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabel was born about 1197, in Hoby, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Anketin de Houby."},"et":{"Abt 1197–":"umbes 1197–Surnud","1199–1265":"1199–1265","1223–1296":"1223–1296","1197–Female":"1197–Surnud","Abt 1197":"umbes 1197","1223":"1223","1265":"1265","1199":"1199","1197":"1197","1296":"1296","Hoby, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Hoby, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", Hoby, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Hoby, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1197–":"noin 1197–Kuollut","1199–1265":"1199–1265","1223–1296":"1223–1296","1197–Female":"1197–Kuollut","Abt 1197":"noin 1197","1223":"1223","1265":"1265","1199":"1199","1197":"1197","1296":"1296","Hoby, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Hoby, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", Hoby, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Hoby, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1197–":"environ 1197–Décédée","1199–1265":"1199–1265","1223–1296":"1223–1296","1197–Female":"1197–Décédée","Abt 119